description: CBI conducted searches at multiple residences in Raipur and Bhilai in connection with the Mahadev Book app betting scam. Among those searched were former CM Bhupesh Baghel's residence and those of several top officials. The operation encompassed 60 locations across multiple states.

description: Khar police issued a second notice to comedian Kunal Kamra for not appearing in a defamation case filed by deputy CM Eknath Shinde, who was alluded to as 'gaddar' in Kamra's video. description: Kerala chief secretary Sarada Muraleedharan confronted a racially insulting remark about her skin colour, responding with a powerful message against societal biases. description: Indian and Chinese officials continued their discussions in Beijing to restart dialogue mechanisms and improve bilateral relations. Both sides agreed to enhance people-to-people exchanges, including direct flights and media interactions. Plans to resume the Kailash Manasarovar Yatra in 2025 were also advanced.

They obtained CCTV footage, but preliminary analysis showed no unauthorized entry. Two senior officers reviewed call and internet details of the judge's cellphone. The fire, which occurred on March 14, is being investigated by police and fire department.

The release of violent Islamic extremists has also been termed a significant threat to security.

description: The Karnataka high court has recommended action against a city civil judge in Bengaluru for referencing non-existent Supreme Court judgments in a ruling. The case involves plaintiffs who sought injunctions against lenders. The high court has asked for an investigation and appropriate action.

title: Chennai police kill snatcher from Maharashtra gang

description: US President Donald Trump announced a 25% tariff on imported autos starting April 2, affecting foreign-made cars and light trucks. This move aims to boost US manufacturing but could strain trade relations with key partners like Japan, Germany, and Canada. The tariffs may increase car prices and impact consumer demand and employment in the auto sector. Trump's broader tariff plans also target pharmaceuticals and semiconductors.

The court upheld the temporary block on expulsions, reinforcing that migrants must have a chance to challenge their alleged gang affiliations in the US before deportation.

title: MNS workers slap store employee in Mumbai for not speaking in Marathi

description: Gujarat Titans captain Shubman Gill's decision to not include Washington Sundar in the playing XI has sparked questions among fans and even caught the attention of Google CEO Sundar Pichai. Meanwhile, Gujarat Titans faced an 11-run defeat against Punjab Kings, despite commendable efforts from Sai Sudharsan and Jos Buttler.
title: Pichai in disbelief over Washington Sundar's poor IPL stock

description: The Supreme Court has stayed the Allahabad High Court’s order that ruled ‘grabbing breast and breaking pyjama string’ as inadequate to charge for rape or attempt to rape. The bench noted the insensitivity of the High Court's handling. The case involved two men assaulting a minor girl.
title: 'Total insensitivity': SC stays Allahabad HC's 'grabbing breasts not rape attempt' order

description: Neha Kakkar faced boos at a Melbourne concert for arriving three hours late and falling on stage. Despite frequent teasing due to her emotions, she and her family overcame many hardships. Her brother Tony revealed in their show that their parents considered aborting Neha due to financial struggles. Their story highlights the challenges their family faced to achieve success.
title: When Tony Kakkar rapped about how parents wanted to abort Neha

description: Stand-up comedian Kunal Kamra requested Khar police for a one-week extension to appear regarding a defamation FIR over a satirical video about Dy CM Eknath Shinde. Meanwhile, political tensions rise as Kamra faces additional complaints and ongoing security measures at a vandalized hotel linked to his performance.
title: Joke row: After Mumbai police notice, Kunal Kamra seeks a week’s time to appear

description: NPCI has announced new UPI security guidelines effective from April 1, 2025, mandating banks and PSPs to use the Mobile Number Revocation List/Digital Intelligence Platform to update databases weekly. The guidelines aim to curb errors caused by inactive mobile numbers and enhance transaction security.
title: New UPI rules starting April 1: Here’s what’s changing

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath launched sharp attacks on Congress leader Rahul Gandhi, labeling him a 'namuna' and criticizing his Bharat Jodo Yatra. Adityanath accused the Congress party of hindering India's development and praised PM Modi for achievements like the Ram Mandir construction.
title: 'Rahul jaise kuch namune rehne chahiye': Yogi Adityanath's dig at LoP

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, BSE Sensex and Nifty50, opened in green on Wednesday. While BSE Sensex went above 78,100, Nifty50 was above 23,700.
title: Sensex over 100 points up; Nifty50 above 23,700

description: Russia and Ukraine agree to halt strikes on energy facilities for 30 days as part of a temporary moratorium. The deal, mediated by the US, aims to ensure safe navigation in the Black Sea amidst ongoing conflicts, with potential to be extended mutually.
title: US claims to have brokered Black Sea ceasefire with Ukraine, Russia: What’s in the deal?

description: Ahmedabad and Gandhinagar have proposed hosting the 2036 Summer Olympics, with projected costs ranging from Rs 34,700 cr to Rs 64,000 cr. The plan includes four additional cities: Bhopal, Goa, Mumbai, and Pune. The ambitious budget surpasses that of Paris 2024, but there are possibilities to optimize costs.
title: Ahmedabad 2036 Olympic bid carries Rs 34k-64k crore tag

description: The Central Bureau of Investigation raided the residences of former Chhattisgarh Chief Minister Bhupesh Baghel, seizing Rs 30 lakh in cash. The raids are linked to an alleged liquor scam that reportedly caused a loss of Rs 2,161 crore to the state exchequer. The Enforcement Directorate previously conducted a similar raid at Baghel's residence.
title: CBI raids Bhupesh Baghel's residence; former Chhattisgarh CM reacts

description: During the Mangla Julus procession for Ram Navami in Hazaribagh, Jharkhand, a scuffle and mild stone pelting occurred between two groups. The conflict arose over objectionable songs played by one group. Authorities swiftly intervened, restoring peace. Deputy Commissioner Nancy Sahay confirmed the situation is now peaceful and under control.
title: Clashes erupt in Jharkhand's Hazaribag over songs played during Mangla Julus

description: The relationship between Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce may face its first challenge with Kelce’s potential invitation to the White House by Donald Trump. Given Swift's strong public opposition to Trump, Kelce's attendance could be a source of tension between the couple.
title: Donald Trump’s invitation to Kansas City Chiefs could put Kelce-Swift relation to test

description: Donald Trump has signed an executive order to overhaul elections in his country, citing 'failure to enforce basic protections.' The order requires states to share voter lists with federal agencies and mandates documentary proof of citizenship for voters. Legal challenges are anticipated based on states' constitutional authority over elections.
title: Highlights of Trump’s executive order reshaping US elections, with a mention of India

description: Harmeet Desai, inspired by the success of 'Gully Boy,' focuses on the present moment in his table tennis career. Despite early challenges in Surat and later gaining high-level coaching in Sweden, his dedication remains strong. Now married and mature, he challenges the notion that sports is only for the wealthy, highlighting India's improved sports infrastructure.
title: 'Overcrowded dining hall, no ACs': Desai recalls Paris Olympics

description: Argentina secured a spot in the 2026 World Cup with a resounding 4-1 victory over Brazil in Buenos Aires, thanks to goals from Julian Alvarez, Enzo Fernandez, Alexis Mac Allister, and Giuliano Simeone. Bolivia's earlier draw confirmed Argentina's qualification. In other matches, Ecuador remain on track, while Colombia and Venezuela also fight for qualification spots.
title: Watch: Argentina thrash Brazil 4-1 to qualify for World Cup
Watch: Motorcyclist plunges into sinkhole that appeared out of nowhere in Seoul

description: Belgian authorities are closely tracking fugitive Indian businessman Mehul Choksi's case as he reportedly left Antigua for medical treatment, while retaining his Antiguan citizenship. Reports suggest Choksi is in Antwerp with his wife and may use forged documents to acquire Belgian residency. Indian and Antiguan governments continue to cooperate on the case.
title: 'Case being handled with significant attention': Belgium govt on Mehul Choksi

description: Punjab Kings defeated Gujarat Titans by 11 runs in a high-scoring IPL-2025 match on Tuesday, thanks to Shreyas Iyer’s unbeaten 97 off 42 balls. Key contributions from Shashank Singh and Priyansh Arya helped Punjab post a formidable total of 243/5. Despite a valiant effort by Gujarat, they fell short in the chase.
title: Shreyas Iyer is Punjab King!

description: A junior staff member accidentally added Jeffrey Goldberg to a classified Signal group chat discussing US military operations against the Houthis. Trump and national security adviser Mike Waltz assured that no classified information was compromised. The administration plans to limit the use of Signal for sharing sensitive information.
title: Signal war chat leak: Trump discloses who added Atlantic editor in the group

description: Stock market recommendations: Mehul Kothari from Anand Rathi Shares recommends buying stocks of RBL Bank, FirstCry, and Voltamp Transformers due to bullish signals and strong support levels.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for March 26, 2025
Trump says Russia wants to end war with Ukraine but could be dragging its feet

description: Astronauts depend on oxygen tanks while in space, with backup systems in place to prevent emergencies. In the event of an oxygen supply failure, emergency tanks and portable cylinders provide a temporary solution. Spacecraft and spacesuits are equipped with systems to maintain a safe breathing environment, but prompt action is crucial to ensure astronauts' survival.
title: What happens if astronauts run out of oxygen in space?

description: BNP secretary general Mirza Fakhrul Islam Alamgir expressed concerns over efforts to downplay the significance of the 1971 Liberation War, warning that such attempts threaten Bangladesh's independence. Fakhrul highlighted that some groups are trying to erase the war from memory and distort history, emphasizing the need to preserve the nation's historical events for younger generations.
title: Eye on polls, BNP worries over bid to erase legacy of 1971 war

description: Five days after claiming in Karnataka assembly that he and other politicians across party lines had been honeytrapped, state cooperation minister K N Rajanna formally submitted a plea with home minister G Parameshwara seeking legal action. However, the HM was evasive on the issue, saying speaker U T Khader's assistance was necessary to initiate any action.
title: Karnataka mantri files honeytrap complaint, puts govt in a spot

description: CLSA maintains high conviction on Bandhan Bank with enhancements in secured assets and technology as key priorities. Jefferies retains 'buy' on Infosys but reduces target price due to slower growth. HDFC Securities recommends DLF for its leadership in luxury real estate, and UBS and ICICI have positive outlooks for Shyam Metalics & Energy and Suven Pharmaceuticals respectively.
title: Stock recommendations by brokers for March 26

description: A mesmerizing blue spiral in the night sky from the UK to Poland on March 24 was linked to a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket launch. It resulted from the rocket's frozen exhaust plume spinning and reflecting sunlight, confirmed by experts and the UK Met Office.
title: SpaceX rocket leaves 'mesmerising' blue spiral seen in night sky across Europe

description: Lawyers at Allahabad high court shut down judicial work Tuesday, launching an indefinite protest against the transfer of Delhi HC's Justice Yashwant Varma to their court. Repatriation is a reward, the bar association said.
title: Allahabad HC lawyers strike work, slam 'betrayal' by judiciary's decision-makers

description: Canada's security intelligence official has flagged India, along with China, Russia, and Pakistan, as potential interferers in the upcoming Canadian elections on April 28. This comes amidst efforts to rebuild India-Canada relations after tensions rose due to allegations involving a Khalistani separatist's murder.
title: Canada: India has intent & capability to interfere in polls

description: The family of M Megha, a 24-year-old IB officer found dead on a railway track in Thiruvananthapuram, has filed a complaint seeking an investigation into her death. While police suspect suicide due to a recent breakup, her family maintains she had no reason to be near the tracks. Megha’s mobile phone will undergo forensic analysis.
title: IB officer found dead on rail tracks in Kerala; police probe ordered
Khar cops issue notice to Kunal Kamra; action causes reaction, says Eknath Shinde
SC to speaker: Why no decision on defecting BRS MLAs after 1 yr?

description: President Trump confirmed a staff error added The Atlantic’s Jeffrey Goldberg to a confidential Signal chat about a Yemen strike. Despite calls for resignations, Trump defended national security advisor Mike Waltz, asserting no significant information was compromised, and the Houthi targets were successfully struck.
title: Trump discloses how journalist ended up in government officials' Signal group
Trump says some countries may get tariff exemptions
Tunnel collapse: Second body, of missing engineer, found

description: President Trump and US intelligence officials scrambled to contain a scandal following an accidental leak involving air strikes on Yemen’s Houthi rebels. The breach occurred when a journalist was mistakenly added to a group chat on Signal, though no classified information was reportedly divulged.
title: US security blunder reveals Trump top team disparaging Europe allies
